## 7. Scoped Sub-Projects

### 7.1 QuickBooks Data Quality Remediation (rerun after the matching has been improved

**Problem:** The current QuickBooks-to-ClickUp match rate is 54.8%, driven by missing `covr_id` values on QuickBooks customer records. This gap prevents accurate financial data from being joined to the Customer Cube for a significant portion of the customer base.

**Interim Solution:** Manually enter `covr_id` values into QuickBooks customer records via the QuickBooks UI. This is a one-time remediation effort for existing records.

**Long-Term Solution:** Evaluate the QuickBooks API to determine whether `covr_id` can be written back automatically when a new customer is created, eliminating the need for manual entry going forward.

**Owner:** Austin (coordination), Engineering (API evaluation)**Definition of Done:** QuickBooks match rate ≥ 95% against ClickUp records.

### 7.2 New Customer ID Propagation Workflow

**Problem:** When a new customer is created in Covr, there is currently no automated process to ensure their `CovrID` is consistently populated across ClickUp, Intercom, and PostHog. This creates the same fragmentation problem over time even as the current backlog is remediated.

**Solution:** Implement an automated workflow triggered by a **Closed Won deal event in HubSpot**. When a deal reaches Closed Won status, the workflow will:

1. Identify all referenced entities on the deal — the **Company** record, the **Corporation** record, and all associated **Contacts**.

1. Generate or retrieve the `CovrID` for each entity.

1. Write the `CovrID` back to the corresponding ClickUp records (company, corporation, and each contact) via the ClickUp API.

1. Propagate the `CovrID` to the matching records in **Intercom** and **PostHog**.

1. The next daily Airbyte sync will pick up the updated identifiers across all systems, ensuring the Customer Cube record is fully resolved within 24 hours of deal close.

