## 9. Risks & Mitigation

| Risk | Likelihood | Impact | Mitigation |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| **Competing engineering priorities** delay pipeline work | Medium | High | Secure dedicated sprint allocation; treat data warehouse as a named engineering project with a ClickUp milestone |
| **QuickBooks API limitations** prevent automated ID write-back | Medium | Medium | Manual UI entry as interim; evaluate API in parallel without blocking dashboard delivery |
| **Scope creep** from department dashboard requests | High | Medium | Lock Phase 3 dashboard scope to documented must-haves; new requests enter a backlog for Phase 4+ |
| **Data quality issues** in source systems surface during modeling | Medium | High | Build validation checks into the transformation layer; flag anomalies in a data quality dashboard |
| **Austin's limited visibility into product data** (PostHog / CovrDB) | Medium | Medium | Schedule working sessions with Product team and Engineering to map PostHog event taxonomy before schema build |
| **HubSpot workflow automation complexity** for ID propagation | Low | High | Scope the workflow in a dedicated engineering spike before committing to a timeline |

